cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.NI 

Reasoning: The paper deals with information theory and cryptography, specifically in the context of wiretap channels and Gelfand-Pinsker channels. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses security and privacy, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions multiuser broadcasting scenarios, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the wiretap-GP analogy as a research tool, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
